HEADWORD: Zircofluoride
<hw>Zir`co*flu"or*ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A double fluoride of zirconium and hydrogen, or
some other positive element or radical; <as>as, <ex>zircofluoride</ex>
of sodium</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
